fields.name: Peter Jepson
fields.notes:
https://antiquesatlas.com/antique/peter_jepson_b_1936_watercolour_pastel_leopard/as237a938
PETER JEPSON, who was born in North West London in 1936, took up painting after his National Service as a hobby and it became his life. He eventually became a full time painter and his subjects were an eclectic mix painted exclusively in oil. He then developed this mixed media technique using pastel and watercolours and turned to wildlife painting.

He had a one man exhibition in New York in 1993 and subsequently had some good sales of his paintings at Christies in London. He was selected a Member of the British Society of Painters in 1990, and is a Fellow of the Society of Artists.
